\f0\fs42 \cf2 \cb3 Luscious Raspberry Curd\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl560\sa80\ql\qnatural

\b\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl340\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}1/2 cup unsalted butter 
\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}1 pint ripe raspberries ( or 12 oz. pkg. frozen raspberries, thawed) 
\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}5 large egg yolks, lightly beaten 
\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}3/4 cup sugar 
\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}salt, a pinch 
\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}2 -3 teaspoons fresh lemon juice 
\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl560\ql\qnatural

\fs34 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl340\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	1.	}Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat; add in the raspberries, egg yolks, sugar, and salt. 
\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	2.	}Cook, mashing the berries and stirring frequently at first and then constantly at the end, until thickened\'97about 10 minutes. 
\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	3.	}Pour the mixture through a coarse strainer set over a bowl, pressing hard on the solids to extract as much liquid as possible. 
\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	4.	}Cool to room temperature; the curd will continue to thicken as it cools. 
\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	5.	}Stir in lemon juice, to taste. 
\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf2 {\listtext	6.	}Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve, or up to 1 month.
